                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.00/747.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-12-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 4, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">[Telegram transmitted to the Secretary of State Dec. 4, 1911.]</p>
                <p>The <hi rend="italic">Nanshan</hi> fired at from Kiukiang forts; the error has
                    been admitted. I have directed the <hi rend="italic">Albany’s</hi> commanding
                    officer to investigate and if necessary obtain an apology.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Murdock.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
